STORER, Appellant, v. DAVID JONES CO., Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. February 16, 1894.) Action by John Storer against the David Jones Company.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JJ.

D. Gerber, for appellant. E. H. Kelly, for respondent.

No opinion. Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
